# Core Standards

- Keep changes scoped to the requested feature, bug or refactor.
- Do not commit secrets, tokens, private keys, real `.env` files or Terraform variable files with sensitive values.
- Prefer existing project patterns over introducing new abstractions.
- Update docs, tests, mocks and configuration when behavior or contracts change.
- Preserve the separation between `frontend/`, `backend/`, `infrastructure/`, `docs/`, `.cursor/` and `cursor/`.
- Use `project.config.json` as the source of truth for how the project was generated.

